definition: strip/item/article/clause (of law or treaty)/classifier for long thin things (ribbon, river, road, trousers etc)

sentences.english: Of panes of glass fixed in place by means of thin strips of lead .
sentences.chinese: 用細小的鉛條來固定在適當的位置上。

sentences.english: It used a lead wire weight at tip . On surface is white PVC Shrink Tubing.
sentences.chinese: 翼尖有鉛條配重，表面蒙乳白色熱縮膜。

sentences.english: The next invention was a machine that made letters of lead when person typed.
sentences.chinese: 另一個發明是帶字母的鉛條打字機器。

sentences.english: The lead was melted and re-used repeatedly.
sentences.chinese: 這種鉛條可以融化再重複使用。
